                            {
                                "id": "193:2014",
                                "name": "Explanation of Fee Allocation: If players A, B, C place 40 chips, 40 chips, 20 chips in the pot, the total pot is 100 chips. A is the winner, B and C are the losers. The chips of players A, B, C put into the pot divide the total bet by 40%, 40%, 20%, the fee is 5% of the bet. So the total fee is 5 chips. 1. If you set the fee allocation to 0%, the fee will be distributed between players according to the number of chips they put in the pot, so the fee charged per player is: Player A: 5 x 40% = 2 Player B: 5 x 40% = 2 Player C: 5 x 20% = 1 2. If you set the fee distribution to 60%, then 60% of the total fees will be distributed only to the losers, the remaining 40% of the total fees will be distributed between winners and losers according to the number of chips that they put it in the pot. In this case, players B and C are losers, the losers put a total of 60 chips into the pot, player B puts 2/3 of 60 chips into the pot, player C puts 1 in the pot. /3 of 60 chips, so the fee charged to a loser is: Player B: 5 x 60% x 2/3 + 5 x 40% x 40% = 2.8 Player C: 5 x 60% x 1/3 + 5 x 40% x 20% = 1.4",
